        <div class="num">N°02 — the salt</div>
        <h2>We went to Korea<br>looking for <em>jugyeom.</em></h2>
        <p>The salt is the formula. Every other electrolyte brand starts with the same industrial sea salt — same source, same mineral profile, same ceiling on performance. So we kept asking: <strong>what salt would change the answer?</strong></p>
        <p>The answer was 1,000 years old, in a small Korean kiln, with a tradition called <em>jugyeom</em> — bamboo salt. Sea salt packed into bamboo stalks, sealed with clay, fired at 1,500°C, then done again. <strong>Nine times.</strong></p>
        <p>The result: pH 12, 70+ trace minerals, and uniquely among foods on Earth — hydroxyl ions that support cellular antioxidant activity.</p>
